# </> Blog

A clean, responsive personal blog built using **Vite**, **Tailwind CSS**, and **vanilla JavaScript**. This project is designed to showcase blog posts, thoughts, and commentary — all wrapped in a simple, lightweight front-end architecture.

---
LINK : youdaheblog.netlify.app

## ✨ Features

- 🔥 Fast Vite-based dev environment
- 🎨 Tailwind CSS styling with dark mode support
- 🧠 Data-driven post rendering from `posts.js`
- 🧾 Responsive blog cards and intro section
- 💡 Clean file structure for easy expansion

---

## 📁 File Structure
blog/
├── index.html            # Main HTML entry
├── src/
│   ├── assets/           # Images and icons
│   ├── components/       # JS components (e.g. Navbar, PostCard)
│   ├── data/
│   │   ├── posts.js      # Blog post data
│   │   └── user.js       # Intro section data
│   ├── styles/
│   │   └── index.css     # Tailwind directives
│   └── main.js           # App entry point
├── public/               # Static assets
├── tailwind.config.js
├── postcss.config.js
├── package.json
└── README.md
---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### 1. Clone the repo
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/blog.git
cd blog
2. Install dependencies
	npm install
3. Start the dev server
	npm run dev



